    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a 2D atmospheric composition profile with altitude (quantitative, interval scale 0-1000 km) vs. gas fractions (quantitative, ratio scale 0-100%). Synthetic data follows established atmospheric stratification patterns: mean molecular weight decreases with altitude (\u03bc=29 at surface \u2192 \u03bc=2 in exosphere) while light gases (H/He) show exponential growth above 500 km. The areaspline visualization maximizes data-ink ratio through continuous opacity gradients and perceptual color ordering (cool \u2192 warm hues for heavy \u2192 light gases). Cairo's principles are applied through proportional stacking (total 100% at all altitudes) and pre-attentive color coding. Statistical validity is maintained through altitude-dependent distributions (surface: N\u2082=78%\u00b11, O\u2082=21%\u00b10.5; thermosphere: O/He dominance with \u03c3=15% variability)."
